00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:12.619
I assume from high school you
know how to add and multiply

00:00:12.619 --> 00:00:17.549
complex numbers using the
relation i squared equals

00:00:17.549 --> 00:00:23.070
negative one.
I'm a little less certain that

00:00:23.070 --> 00:00:29.084
you remember how to divide them.
I hope you read last night by

00:00:29.084 --> 00:00:34.408
way of preparation for that,
but since that's something

00:00:34.408 --> 00:00:40.225
we're going to have to do a lot
of a differential equations,

00:00:40.225 --> 00:00:45.845
so remember that the division
is done by making use of the

00:00:45.845 --> 00:00:50.953
complex conjugate.
So, if z is equal to a plus bi,

00:00:50.953 --> 00:00:53.948
some people write a plus ib,

00:00:53.948 --> 00:00:57.204
and sometimes I'll do
that too if it's more

00:00:57.204 --> 00:00:59.874
convenient.
Then, the complex conjugate is

00:00:59.874 --> 00:01:03.000
what you get by changing i to
negative i.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:06.792
And, the important thing is
that the product of those two is

00:01:06.792 --> 00:01:09.299
a real number.
The product of these is a

00:01:09.299 --> 00:01:13.157
squared minus the quantity ib
all squared,

00:01:13.157 --> 00:01:16.950
which makes a squared plus b
squared because i

00:01:16.950 --> 00:01:19.264
squared is negative one.

00:01:19.264 --> 00:01:22.864
So, the product of those,
that's what you multiply if you

00:01:22.864 --> 00:01:26.078
want to multiply this by
something to make it real.

00:01:26.078 --> 00:01:30.000
You always multiplied by its
complex conjugate.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:34.089
And that's the trick that
underlines the doing of the

00:01:34.089 --> 00:01:36.056
division.
So, for example,

00:01:36.056 --> 00:01:40.303
I better hang onto these or
I'll never remember all the

00:01:40.303 --> 00:01:42.662
examples.
Suppose, for example,

00:01:42.662 --> 00:01:47.224
we wanted to calculate (two
plus i) divided by (one minus 3

00:01:47.224 --> 00:01:51.707
i).
To calculate it means I want to

00:01:51.707 --> 00:01:55.404
do the division;
I want to express the answer in

00:01:55.404 --> 00:02:00.480
the form a plus bi.
What you do is multiply the top

00:02:00.480 --> 00:02:04.959
and bottom by the complex
conjugate of the denominator in

00:02:04.959 --> 00:02:09.120
order to make it real.
So, it's (one plus 3i) divided

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:14.080
by (one plus 3i),
as they taught you in

00:02:14.080 --> 00:02:16.479
elementary school,
that is one,

00:02:16.479 --> 00:02:20.879
in a rather odd notation;
therefore, multiplying doesn't

00:02:20.879 --> 00:02:23.439
change the value of the
fraction.

00:02:23.439 --> 00:02:27.520
And so, the denominator now
becomes 1 squared plus 3

00:02:27.520 --> 00:02:32.000
squared, which is ten.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:35.723
And, the numerator is,
learn to do this without

00:02:35.723 --> 00:02:40.338
multiplying out four terms.
You must be able to do this in

00:02:40.338 --> 00:02:43.414
your head.
And, you always do it by the

00:02:43.414 --> 00:02:48.352
grouping, or post office method,
whatever you want to call it,

00:02:48.352 --> 00:02:53.290
namely, first put down the real
part, which is made out of two

00:02:53.290 --> 00:02:57.823
times one minus three times one.
So, that's negative one.

00:02:57.823 --> 00:03:01.871
And then, the imaginary part,
which is i times one.

00:03:01.871 --> 00:03:06.000
That's one, coefficient one,
plus 6i.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:09.396
So, that makes 7i.
Now, some people feel this

00:03:09.396 --> 00:03:12.252
still doesn't look right,
if you wish,

00:03:12.252 --> 00:03:15.803
and for some places and
differential equations,

00:03:15.803 --> 00:03:20.435
it will be useful to write that
as minus one tenth plus seven

00:03:20.435 --> 00:03:24.757
tenths i.
And, now it's perfectly clear

00:03:24.757 --> 00:03:30.176
that it's in the form a plus bi.
So, learn to do that if you

00:03:30.176 --> 00:03:33.884
don't know already.
It's going to be important.

00:03:33.884 --> 00:03:38.156
Now, the main thing today is
the polar representation,

00:03:38.156 --> 00:03:42.026
which sometimes they don't get
to in high school.

00:03:42.026 --> 00:03:45.411
And if they do,
it's usually not in a grown

00:03:45.411 --> 00:03:49.200
up-enough in a form for us to be
able to use it.

00:03:49.200 --> 00:03:52.505
So, I have to worry about that
little bit.

00:03:52.505 --> 00:03:56.777
The polar representation,
of course, is nominally just

00:03:56.777 --> 00:04:00.969
the switch to polar coordinates.
If here's a plus bi,

00:04:00.969 --> 00:04:05.000
then this is r,
and that's theta.

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:07.968
And therefore,
this can be written as,

00:04:07.968 --> 00:04:11.659
in the polar form,
that would be r cosine theta

00:04:11.659 --> 00:04:15.590
plus i, or r cosine theta.

00:04:15.590 --> 00:04:18.077
That's the A part.

00:04:18.077 --> 00:04:21.446
And, the B part is,
the imaginary part is r

00:04:21.446 --> 00:04:24.415
sin(theta) times i.

00:04:24.415 --> 00:04:27.704
Now, it would be customary,
at this point,

00:04:27.704 --> 00:04:33.000
to put the i in front,
just because it looks better.

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:36.357
The complex numbers are
commutative, satisfied to

00:04:36.357 --> 00:04:38.665
commutative law of
multiplication,

00:04:38.665 --> 00:04:42.722
which means it doesn't matter
in multiplication whether you

00:04:42.722 --> 00:04:46.359
put i in front or behind.
It's still the same answer.

00:04:46.359 --> 00:04:50.345
So, this would be r cosine
theta plus i times 

00:04:50.345 --> 00:04:52.654
r sine theta,

00:04:52.654 --> 00:04:54.962
which, of course,
will factor out,

00:04:54.962 --> 00:04:59.228
and will make it cosine theta
plus i sine theta.

00:04:59.228 --> 00:05:02.376
Now, it was Euler who took the

00:05:02.376 --> 00:05:05.943
decisive step and said,
hey, look, I'm going to call

00:05:05.943 --> 00:05:10.000
that e to the i theta.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:15.586
Now, why did he do that?
Because everything seemed to

00:05:15.586 --> 00:05:21.388
indicate that it should.
But that's certainly worth the

00:05:21.388 --> 00:05:24.933
best color we have,
which is what?

00:05:24.933 --> 00:05:29.446
We are getting low here.
Okay, nonetheless,

00:05:29.446 --> 00:05:34.280
it's worth pink.
I will even give him his due,

00:05:34.280 --> 00:05:38.184
Euler.
Sometimes it's called Euler's

00:05:38.184 --> 00:05:40.820
formula, but it really shouldn't
be.

00:05:40.820 --> 00:05:43.607
It's not a formula.
It's a definition.

00:05:43.607 --> 00:05:46.771
So, in some sense,
you can't argue with it.

00:05:46.771 --> 00:05:50.914
If you want to call putting a
complex number in a power,

00:05:50.914 --> 00:05:53.023
and calling it that,
you can.

00:05:53.023 --> 00:05:56.036
But, one can certainly ask why
he did it.

00:05:56.036 --> 00:05:58.974
And the answer,
I guess, is that all the

00:05:58.974 --> 00:06:03.493
evidence seemed to point to the
fact that it was the thing to

00:06:03.493 --> 00:06:07.224
do.
Now, I think it's important to

00:06:07.224 --> 00:06:10.487
talk about a little bit because
I think it's,

00:06:10.487 --> 00:06:13.676
in my opinion,
if you're seeing this for the

00:06:13.676 --> 00:06:17.235
first time, even if you read
about it last night,

00:06:17.235 --> 00:06:21.092
it's a mysterious thing,
and one needs to see it from

00:06:21.092 --> 00:06:25.541
every possible point of view.
It's something you get used to.

00:06:25.541 --> 00:06:29.249
You will never see it in a
sudden flash of insight.

00:06:29.249 --> 00:06:33.773
It will just get as familiar to
you as more common arithmetic,

00:06:33.773 --> 00:06:38.000
and algebraic,
and calculus processes are.

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:40.583
But, look.
What is it we demand?

00:06:40.583 --> 00:06:44.583
If you're going to call
something an exponential,

00:06:44.583 --> 00:06:47.833
what is it we want an
exponential to do,

00:06:47.833 --> 00:06:52.916
what gives an expression like
this the right to be called e to

00:06:52.916 --> 00:06:57.500
the i theta?
The answer is I can't creep

00:06:57.500 --> 00:07:01.937
inside Euler's mind.
It must have been a very big

00:07:01.937 --> 00:07:04.774
day of his life.
He had a lot of big days,

00:07:04.774 --> 00:07:08.925
but when he realized that that
was the thing to write down as

00:07:08.925 --> 00:07:12.385
the definition of e to the i
theta.

00:07:12.385 --> 00:07:15.360
But, what is it one wants of an
exponential?

00:07:15.360 --> 00:07:19.512
Well, the high school answer
surely is you want it to satisfy

00:07:19.512 --> 00:07:22.072
the exponential law.
Now, to my shock,

00:07:22.072 --> 00:07:24.563
