00:07:51.262 --> 00:07:54.549
the law of exponents.

00:07:54.549 --> 00:07:59.928
That's the most important
reason why, that's the single

00:07:59.928 --> 00:08:05.605
most important thing about
exponents, are the way one uses

00:08:05.605 --> 00:08:10.125
them.
And, this is the exponential

00:08:10.125 --> 00:08:16.488
function, called the exponential
function because all this

00:08:16.488 --> 00:08:20.618
significant stuff is in the
exponents.

00:08:20.618 --> 00:08:25.195
All right, so it should
satisfy-- we want,

00:08:25.195 --> 00:08:31.000
first of all,
the exponential law to be true.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:34.605
But that's not all.
That's a high school answer.

00:08:34.605 --> 00:08:38.671
An MIT answer would be,
I mean, why is e to the x such

00:08:38.671 --> 00:08:41.357
a popular function?
Well, of course,

00:08:41.357 --> 00:08:44.962
it does satisfy the exponential
law, but for us,

00:08:44.962 --> 00:08:48.645
an even more reasonable thing.
It's the function,

00:08:48.645 --> 00:08:53.171
which, when you differentiate
it, you get the same thing you

00:08:53.171 --> 00:08:56.547
started with.
